table asyncio_extra194.asyncio_condition_init_waitfor_qualnames:
  description: "asyncio.Condition __init__ and wait_for qualname identity in asynciocond194 namespace — Condition.__init__.__qualname__=='Condition.__init__' (len=18: 'Condition'=9+'.'=1+'__init__'=8=18; Condition.__init__ accepts an optional lock parameter, defaulting to a new asyncio.Lock()); Condition.wait_for.__qualname__=='Condition.wait_for' (len=18: 'Condition'=9+'.'=1+'wait_for'=8=18; waits until predicate() returns a truthy value, calling wait() in a loop); Condition.__init__.__qualname__ (18) == Condition.wait_for.__qualname__ (18) — identical lengths despite different method roles; both are shorter than Condition.notify_all.__qualname__ (20) and longer than Condition.notify.__qualname__ (16); verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
